# Project Context Index: {project-name}
# generated: auto — regenerate with: bash scripts/generate-context-index.sh --project {project-name}
> Where to find and store project-specific information (N4)

## Configuration
[location] CLAUDE.md — project config, stack, environments
[intent: "what stack does this project use"] → CLAUDE.md

## Business Rules
[location] reglas-negocio.md — business rules with RN-XXX codes
[location] business-rules/ — detailed rule documents
[intent: "what are the business rules for X"] → reglas-negocio.md
[digest-target] When extracting rules from meetings/docs → reglas-negocio.md

## Team & Stakeholders
[location] team/TEAM.md — team composition and roles
[location] team/stakeholders/ — external stakeholder profiles
[location] equipo.md — team structure (legacy format)
[intent: "who works on this project"] → team/TEAM.md or equipo.md
[digest-target] When extracting people info from meetings → team/

## Meetings & Decisions
[location] meetings/ — meeting digests and transcripts
[location] decision-log.md — architectural and business decisions
[location] _digest-log.md — digest traceability log
[intent: "what was decided about X"] → decision-log.md
[digest-target] When processing meeting transcripts → meetings/
[digest-target] When extracting decisions → decision-log.md

## Architecture & Technical
[location] ARCHITECTURE.md — system architecture overview
[location] specs/ — SDD specifications
[location] adrs/ — architecture decision records
[intent: "how is the system designed"] → ARCHITECTURE.md
[digest-target] When extracting technical decisions → adrs/

## Analysis & Reports
[location] analysis/ — business analysis outputs
[location] security/ — security audit results
[location] diagrams/ — architecture and flow diagrams
[digest-target] When extracting analysis → analysis/

## Backlog
[location] backlog/ — Savia Flow backlog items (if using local flow)
[location] backlog/pbi/ — Product Backlog Items
[location] backlog/specs/ — SDD specs linked to PBIs
[intent: "what is in the backlog"] → backlog/

## Glossary
[location] GLOSSARY.md — project terminology and acronyms
[intent: "what does term X mean"] → GLOSSARY.md
[digest-target] When extracting domain terms → GLOSSARY.md

## Agent Memory (project level)
[location] agent-memory/{agent}/ — project-specific agent knowledge
[digest-target] When agent learns project pattern → agent-memory/{agent}/

## Environments
[location] ENVIRONMENTS.md — environment configuration
[location] config.local/ — secrets per environment (gitignored)
[intent: "what environments exist"] → ENVIRONMENTS.md
